The paper focuses on 3D object detection from 2D images and 3D Lidar point clouds, which is a problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper proposes a novel approach for improving 3D object detection performance, which involves using a two-stage object detection framework with PointNet as the backbone network. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper evaluates its method on the KITTI dataset, which is a popular benchmark for autonomous driving research, indicating that the paper may also be relevant to natural language processing (cs.CL) for tasks related to autonomous driving.
